metadata.name: musical society #530
metadata.description:
society.png: musical society is a collaborative PFP work drawn by Tito Yusuf and directed by Sandy Pirouzi with the aim to facilitate Tezos newcomers with affordable PFP to rock.

This series is taking inspiration from a music scene that Tito is part of. Some traits are paying tribute to some of Tezos musicians such as Jburn, Musical Jackal, Binerica, and Sigmun.

---------------------------------------------

Some are pretending to be us
Some others are even not us
(And few of them are not even alive anymore)
---------------------------------------------

metadata.name: Unicorn #8288
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: Mind docks sorting station #361
metadata.description:
in an altered state,
order tries to get a grasp,
architect is dreaming

#12
experimental vintage series

press "C" to turn on/off outlines
press "V" to turn on/off blocks, if present
press "B" to turn on/off rotation
press "N" to reload with different layout, 3 iterations to cycle through

press "UP arrow" to increase render scale multiplier by x1 (maximum is x4, default is x2)
press "DOWN arrow" to decrease render scale multiplier by x1

press "S" to save png in live view

metadata.name: Colored Elementary Cellular Automaton #323
metadata.description:
The algorithm is based on Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton. 
This is a 1D cellular automaton with a neighborhood of 5 cells. This gives us 2^5 = 32 patterns for a neighborhood and 2^32 = 4.29B possible combinations!!! The size of the cell varies in a range of 2 to 8. There is a 15% of getting a black and white art.

Pattern rarity:
- Pattern 1 _25%
- Pattern 2 _30%
- Pattern 3 _35%
- Pattern 4 _15%

Note: The art might look in different resolutions because of the responsive view, but the color, pattern, and layout remain the same.

metadata.description:
Generative visual composition, hybrid techniques, interactive, textures source created with GAN, assist by AI, eclectic, colors, transform in autonomous system, glitch, made with code, and modular patch.

* Interactive feature :
- place your mouse to visual screen,
- left click to glitch it or see other variations, and
- right click for reset or back to original composition.
